scope.summary:
Bind the native Rust editor layer to the existing /knowledge/code/* backend APIs for symbol navigation, reference graphs, test linkage, citation spans, and the Monaco file lens payload. No backend changes are permitted; this MT is pure frontend wiring.

Goal: create a typed Rust client module at src/frontend/backend/knowledge_code_nav.rs that exposes async functions for all six routes in the backend knowledge_code_nav API. The diff shape is one new file plus a re-export from src/frontend/backend/mod.rs.

The backend HTTP surface (read from handshake_core/src/api/knowledge_code_nav.rs) exposes:
  GET /knowledge/code/symbols                                   -> lookup_symbols
  GET /knowledge/code/symbols/:entity_id                        -> get_symbol
  GET /knowledge/code/symbols/:entity_id/references             -> symbol_references
  GET /knowledge/code/symbols/:entity_id/tests                  -> symbol_tests
  GET /knowledge/code/symbols/:entity_id/spans                  -> symbol_spans
  GET /knowledge/code/files/:path/lens?workspace_id=&content_hash=&parser_version= -> file_lens

All six routes require identity headers:
  x-hsk-actor-id           (required)
  x-hsk-kernel-task-run-id (required)
  x-hsk-session-run-id     (required)
  x-hsk-actor-kind         (optional; default is 'system')
  x-hsk-correlation-id     (optional)
A missing required header returns 400. This is the same header contract as knowledge_documents (MT-037); reuse the HskDocumentHeaders struct or a shared NavHeaders type from the same module or a shared headers.rs.

Response shapes (derived from backend knowledge_code_nav.rs):
  - SymbolNavProjection { symbol_entity_id, symbol_key, display_name, symbol_kind, owning_wp?, primary_source_id?, lifecycle_state, definition?, staleness }
  - DefinitionSpan { span_id, source_id, line_start, line_end, range_start?, range_end?, section_path? }
  - StalenessState { state: String, fresh: bool, indexed_content_hash?, indexed_parser_version?, detail? }
  - SymbolLookupResponse { workspace_id, matches: Vec<SymbolNavProjection>, nav_receipt_event_id, quiet_background_work_receipt_id }
  - SymbolGetResponse { symbol: SymbolNavProjection, nav_receipt_event_id, quiet_background_work_receipt_id }
  - SymbolReferencesResponse { symbol_entity_id, staleness, callers, callees, nav_receipt_event_id, quiet_background_work_receipt_id }
  - SymbolCallerCallee { symbol_entity_id, symbol_key, display_name, confidence, evidence_spans, staleness }
  - EvidenceSpanRef { span_id, line_start, line_end }
  - SymbolTestsResponse { symbol_entity_id, staleness, tests: Vec<SymbolTestEntry>, nav_receipt_event_id, quiet_background_work_receipt_id }
  - SymbolTestEntry { test_entity_id, test_symbol_key, display_name, confidence, evidence_spans, staleness }
  - SymbolSpansResponse { symbol_entity_id, staleness, spans: Vec<SymbolSpan>, nav_receipt_event_id, quiet_background_work_receipt_id }
  - SymbolSpan { span_id, source_id, span_kind, line_start, line_end, range_start?, range_end?, section_path?, content_sha256?, parser_version? }
  - FileLensResponse { relative_path, content_hash, parser_version, entries: Vec<FileLensEntry>, nav_receipt_event_id, quiet_background_work_receipt_id }
  - FileLensEntry { entity_id, entity_key, display_name, symbol_kind, line_start, line_end, caller_count, callee_count, test_count, staleness }

Request parameter types:
  - LookupParams { workspace_id, name?, prefix?, path?, limit? }
  - LensParams { workspace_id, content_hash, parser_version }

Exact files to create/edit:
  - CREATE: src/frontend/backend/knowledge_code_nav.rs
  - EDIT:   src/frontend/backend/mod.rs (add `pub mod knowledge_code_nav;`)

Step-by-step implementation notes:
  1. Reuse or reference the NavHeaders / HskDocumentHeaders type from MT-037 (src/frontend/backend/knowledge_documents.rs). If that MT is not yet merged, define a CodeNavHeaders struct with the same five fields and add a TODO noting consolidation with MT-037.
  2. Implement lookup_symbols: GET with query params workspace_id, name?, prefix?, path?, limit?. At least one of name/prefix/path is required (backend returns 400 otherwise); enforce this with a typed LookupRequest enum or pre-flight check.
  3. Implement get_symbol: GET /knowledge/code/symbols/:entity_id. Uses nav headers.
  4. Implement symbol_references: GET /knowledge/code/symbols/:entity_id/references. Returns callers (incoming REFERENCES edges) and callees (outgoing REFERENCES edges).
  5. Implement symbol_tests: GET /knowledge/code/symbols/:entity_id/tests. Returns tests that have a `validates` edge targeting this symbol.
  6. Implement symbol_spans: GET /knowledge/code/symbols/:entity_id/spans. Returns all citation spans for the symbol.
  7. Implement file_lens: GET /knowledge/code/files/:path/lens?workspace_id=&content_hash=&parser_version=. The :path segment is a repo-relative POSIX path; URL-encode any '/' in the path as %2F when building the URL (the backend decodes %2F and plain / from the path segment). NEVER accept absolute paths or paths with '..' segments from callers.
  8. All responses include nav_receipt_event_id and quiet_background_work_receipt_id which should be preserved in the typed response structs (they are machine-readable audit receipts).
  9. The staleness field is a tagged shape: { state: String, fresh: bool, ... }. Define StalenessState with common fields; unknown extra fields use #[serde(flatten)] or serde_json::Value for the additional detail field.
  10. AccessKit note: this MT creates backend client code only. When a code symbol panel widget is built (porting CodeSymbolPanel.tsx), every interactive element (symbol name button, definition jump link, reference list row, test row, lens entry row) MUST get a stable AccessKit author_id, role (Role::Link or Role::ListItem as appropriate), and actions (Action::Click for navigation). Add this as a doc comment in the file so the widget author sees the requirement.
  11. Register the module in src/frontend/backend/mod.rs.
